# =============================================================================
#  GuardAC — PUBLIC repository = the Minecraft PLUGIN ONLY.
#
#  Strategy: an ALLOWLIST. We ignore EVERYTHING by default, then re-include
#  only the plugin sources. This is deliberate: a stray secret (keys DB, .env,
#  admin token, trained model) can then never leak by accident — anything new
#  dropped into the project is ignored until explicitly whitelisted here.
#
#  NEVER published (all covered by the blanket ignore below):
#    backend/        - private SaaS: PyTorch model, keys DB (plaintext keys +
#                      password hashes), business logic, .env, datasets  = the moat
#    guardac-web/    - website + admin panel + dashboard (.env.local)
#    CLAUDE.md       - internal brief (server IP, secrets, detection internals)
#    .env / *.db / *.pt / *.pem / *.key ...  - secrets & artifacts
# =============================================================================

# 1) Ignore every top-level entry by default.
/*

# 2) Re-include ONLY the plugin (Kotlin) and what is needed to build it.
!/.gitignore
!/.gitattributes
!/.github/
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/build.gradle.kts
!/settings.gradle.kts
!/gradle.properties
!/gradlew
!/gradlew.bat
!/gradle/
!/src/

# 3) Build output that can live inside otherwise-tracked folders.
build/
.gradle/
*.class

# 4) Belt-and-suspenders: these patterns are ignored EVERYWHERE, even if a
#    future edit above accidentally re-includes a folder that contains one.
#    (Deliberately NOT ignoring *.jar so gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar stays.)
.env
*.env
.env.*
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.pt
*.onnx
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.keystore
id_rsa*
*.log
secrets.*
